{
  "brand": "InFocus",
  "device": "PROJECTOR",
  "variant": "InFocus IN112x / IN114x / IN116x / IN118HDxc / IN119HDx (ASCII protocol)",
  "controlType": "RS232",
  "notes": [
    "Source: 'InFocus IN112x/IN114x/IN116x/IN118HDxc/IN119HDx RS232 Control Instructions' (part 009-1595-00).",
    "Wire: D-Sub 9-pin null-modem. 9600 8N1, no flow control.",
    "Format: 3-letter command + value, all enclosed in parens — e.g. (PWR1), (SRC4), (VOL+). No CR/LF needed.",
    "Source codes (SRC): 0=VGA1, 1=VGA2, 4=HDMI, 11=Video, 12=S-Video.",
    "Append '!' before the closing paren to request an echo/status read after write, e.g. (PWR1!).",
    "Timing: 10s delay required after lamp ignition / power down; 3s after source change; 5ms minimum inter-command gap.",
    "Read commands use '?' as the value, e.g. (PWR?). Responses are ASCII strings: (PWR?) -> '0' (off) / '1' (on). (SRC?) -> current source index. (LMP?) -> lamp hours (0-9999, max life 5000). (MTE?) -> '0'/'1'. (VOL?) -> 0-20. (BLK?) -> '0'/'1'. (ARZ?) -> aspect (0=Auto,1=Native,2=4:3,3=16:9,4=Letterbox,6=16:10). (IPM?) -> lamp mode '0'=Normal/'1'=Eco. (MDL?) -> model name string. (VER?) -> firmware version string."
